---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Services
description: "Explore individual and group Portuguese tutoring classes with Manuela in Vancouver — A1 beginners through B2 advanced levels."
---

{% block content %}

<!-- Page Hero -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Classes &amp; Services</h1>
    <p>From your very first word to fluent conversation — there&rsquo;s a class that fits exactly where you are.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Intro -->
<section class="section section--alt">
  <div class="container text-center">
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 700px; margin-inline: auto;">
      All classes are offered in Vancouver, BC, and focus on <strong>European Portuguese</strong> — the authentic accent and dialect spoken in Portugal. Small group sizes ensure personal attention, and individual sessions are fully customised to your goals.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Service Cards -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid-3" style="grid-template-columns: 1fr;">

      {% for service in services %}
      <article class="card" id="{{ service.id }}" style="flex-direction: row; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <div style="flex: 0 0 auto; font-size: 3rem;">{{ service.icon }}</div>
        <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 220px;">
          <span class="card__level">{{ service.level }}</span>
          <h3 style="margin-top: 0.25rem;">{{ service.title }}</h3>
          <p>{{ service.description }}</p>
          <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1rem 0 0;">
            {% for item in service.highlights %}
            <li style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: flex-start; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
              <span style="color: var(--color-primary); flex-shrink: 0;">✓</span>
              {{ item }}
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn--outline-dark mt-md" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Enquire Now</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      {% endfor %}

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CEFR Explainer -->
<section class="section section--alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="cefr-callout">
      <h3>What Do A1, A2, B1, B2 Mean?</h3>
      <p>
        These are levels from the <strong>Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR)</strong> — the international standard used to describe language proficiency. Here&rsquo;s a quick guide:
      </p>
      <div class="cefr-levels">
        <div class="cefr-level"><strong>A1</strong> — Complete beginner. Learning first words and phrases.</div>
        <div class="cefr-level"><strong>A2</strong> — Elementary. Can handle simple, everyday interactions.</div>
        <div class="cefr-level"><strong>B1</strong> — Intermediate. Can manage most travel situations and hold basic conversations.</div>
        <div class="cefr-level"><strong>B2</strong> — Upper intermediate. Can interact fluently with native speakers on familiar topics.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="cta-banner">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Not Sure Which Level Is Right for You?</h2>
    <p>Get in touch and Manuela will help you find the perfect starting point — no pressure, no tests required.</p>
    <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn--white">Get in Touch</a>
  </div>
</section>

{% endblock %}
